com.apriori.collections

Interface BiMap<K,V>

  • Type Parameters:
    K - the type of keys in the map
    V - the type of values in the map
    All Superinterfaces:
    Map<K,V>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    HashBiMap

    public interface BiMap<K,V>
extends Map<K,V>
    A map that defines two-way mappings and whose values are unique. The values are effectively a set. Storing a mapping with a value that is already present may implicitly remove the mapping with which it was previously associated.

    • Method Detail

      • contains

        boolean contains(K key,
                 V value)
        Returns true if the map contains the given mapping. If the map contains the given key, but mapped to a different value, or it contains the given value, but associated with a different key, then this returns false.
        Parameters:
        key - a key
        value - a value
        Returns:
        true if this map contains the given key and it is mapped to the given value
